\pard\intbl\fi-360\li720\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Sacrificing one Bonus Skill Point Pick grants a +5 increase to the value of \b one\b0  Community Bond. \par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Sacrificing further Bonus Picks to the \b same Bond\b0  grants +2 for each extra pick sacrificed. Sacrificing a pick towards a different Bond achieves the full increase stated above.\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Community Bond strengths can only be increased to a maximum of 20 (at which point your Protagonist is the community\rquote s top leader).\par
\pard\intbl\sa120 As an alternative, if you are willing for your Protagonist to set a Community Bond to a value of 1 (ready to break at the slightest provocation, with possibly disastrous social outcome), that sacrifice earns one EXTRA Bonus Skill Point Pick. You can claim this reward multiple times if you wish to set several Community Bonds to 1.\cell\row\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 2.10\tab Detailed Description: Skills\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 A skill represents expertise gained with intensive training or study. If you make a skill roll, your Protagonist is doing something that would leave untrained people lost. \par
\lang3081 Anyone can attempt a \b DEX\'d75\b0  test to avoid being knocked over in the back of an out-of-control wagon; only someone who\rquote s been trained in the proper Drive skill can steer the battered vehicle away from the grasping, tentacled thing tearing at its wheels.\lang1033  \par
Roll your Protagonist\rquote s skill or lower on 1D100 to succeed at using the skill under dire circumstances. Skills improve through practice and experience.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.10.1\tab Base Rating\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Every skill lists its base rating. If a skill has a base rating of 1% or greater, anyone can attempt to use it. A skill at 0% can\rquote t be used at all. No skill can be higher than 99%.\par
