\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.10.2\tab How Skills Work\par
\pard\cf0\b0\f1 For details of specific skills, see the listing in \b SKILL DESCRIPTIONS\b0  starting on page \lang3081 32\lang1033 . \par
When your Protagonist uses a skill, sometimes you roll dice and sometimes you don\rquote t.\par
\b USING A SKILL WITHOUT A ROLL:\b0  When circumstances are calm and controlled, you don\rquote t roll dice to have your Protagonist use a skill; the Game Moderator just needs to know how high your Protagonist\rquote s rating is. \par
\lang3081 For example, controlling a river barge when things are calm might simply require a certain amount the appropriate Sailing skill.\lang1033  \par
Using a skill without rolling means randomness is not a factor. It\rquote s about having the right skill, looking in the right place, and asking the right questions. The more subtle the clue, the higher the skill your Protagonist must have to figure it out.\par
\b USING A SKILL WITH A ROLL:\b0  Roll skill dice only when the outcome is in doubt. That usually means there\rquote s a crisis or the circumstances are not under your Protagonist\rquote s control. The higher the skill rating, the better your Protagonist\rquote s chance of success. For details, see \b USING SKILLS\b0  on page \lang3081 41\lang1033 .\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.10.3\tab Common Knowledge\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Most Protagonists picked up some basic knowledge as they grew up. Because of this, they have some basic understanding of common things like how their society works and what types of jobs do what; and some basic abilities like how to flee danger. These don\rquote t require specific skills. Skills represents deep, specialized training or education, but Protagonists can sometimes get by on common knowledge. Calling on common knowledge requires an \b INT\'d75\b0  test or having a certain level of INT. Charming someone with unskilled art is usually a \b CHA\b0  or \b DEX\b0  test. Other efforts use other stats. The Game Moderator decides whether a task requires the general ability of a stat or the specialization of a skill.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.10.4\tab Improving Skills\par
\pard\cf0\b0\f1 We learn from failure. If your Protagonist has at least 1% in a skill (any except Unnatural), it can improve when your Protagonists attempts to use it and \i fails\i0 . Gaining an entirely new skill requires special training (see \b DOWNTIME \b0 on page \lang3081 80\lang1033 ).\par
On the character sheet, next to every skill except Unnatural, there is a check box. When your Protagonist tries to use a skill and fails, put a checkmark in that skill\rquote s box. At the end of each game session, add 1D4 percentage point to every skill that has a check next to it and erase the check.\par
\b FAILING WITHOUT ROLLING:\b0  If your Protagonist attempts a challenging task that requires a certain level of skill but not a roll, and fails because the task requires more skill than your Protagonist has, put a check in the box.\par
\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.10.5\tab Skill Descriptions\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\b0\i Alchemy\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
Alchemy is pseudo-chemistry wrapped in mysticism designed to prolong life, find a universal cure for disease, turn lead into gold, or any fantastical goal. It draws heavily on ancient sources, wraps them in religious trappings, and bottles it.  Alchemy as a skill is by no means limited to those educated in the classics. Many wise women and cunning men know as much about alchemy as a Palatinate scholar who claims to have studied with the Arabs.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Alertness\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
Alertness detects danger. Use it to hear a weapon being readied, to understand the mumbling on the other side of a wall, to spot a concealed item hidden under a jacket, or to catch someone who is trying to escape notice using Stealth.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Animal Handling\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 Animals are part and parcel of medieval life. Everyone has a basic understanding of caring for and trying to control animals. Animal handling can be used to calm a spooked horse, quiet a barking dog, or even train a squirrel to perform tricks. \par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Animal handling can\rquote t be by a rider to control a mount. That\rquote s the \b Ride\b0  skill.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Appraise\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The ability to quickly determine the true (intrinsic) value of an item. This is an important skill in ensuring that bartering exchange deals are favorable to you. It is also helpful in know what items or resources others might be willing to trade to obtain.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Art (Type)\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Expertise at creating or performing a work that sways emotions and opinions. It also encompasses knowledge of techniques and trends in your field, and the ability tell a particular creator\rquote s real work from a fake. Anyone can draw a rough sketch; the Art skill reflects knowledge, practice, and talent. Each type of Art is a separate skill: Acting, Dance, Forgery, Music, Poetry, Sculpture, Singing, Storytelling, etc.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Athletics\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 30%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Your Protagonist trains to get the most out of his or her strength and agility. Strength and Dexterity cover raw physical power and manual dexterity; the Athletics skill represents long practice doing things like running, jumping, climbing, and throwing.\par
\pard\sl276\slmult1 Use Athletics to:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Outrun someone (see \b OPPOSED TESTS\b0  on page 45).\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Jump an intimidating gap.\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Climb in a crisis.\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Land safely in a fall of up to three yards.\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Hit a target with a thrown knife or put a ceramic grenade exactly on target.\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Catch something without warning, such as intercepting a thrown grenade.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Beguile\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 In the feudal world, oftentimes the best way to convince someone to do what you want them to do, is by appealing to their sense of power or self-importance. This delicate art combines guile, cunning, \ldblquote buttering-up\rdblquote , or other such subtle techniques to curry favor and obtain leverage.\par
Beguiling is not about open threats, teasing, or aggressive bluster \endash  that is covered by the \b Harangue/Taunt\b0  skill. Nor is it about using cold logic to convince them (that\rquote s \b Persuade\b0 ). Rather, this skill is about using wile and cunning, coupled with a detailed understanding of the authority and power wielded by the person, to gain advantage.\par
If the target of the skill starts from an antagonistic viewpoint, some form of \b OPPOSED TEST\b0  will probably be needed to overcome their negative impression. \par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Carouse\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 People have a variety of ways of reveling and relaxing when the work-day is through. This skill combines a knowledge of such social distractions and indulgences, and a practiced skill in partaking \endash  and perhaps excelling \endash  in their practice.\par
Use it to know the particular forms of entertainments that certain classes of society are likely to crave, and the people and places who are able to satisfy them \endash  whether legally or otherwise.\par
When participating in a leisure activity, this skill can be called upon when endurance or skillful practice of the revelry would achieve an advantage. One such use might be retaining one\rquote s faculties even when imbibing excessive intoxicating drinks. Another might be winning at games of chance commonly used for wagering (in this case, the skill is likely to be part of an OPPOSED TEST against other players\rquote  \b Carouse\b0 , with sly attempts at cheating covered by the \b Stealth\b0  skill).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Chirurgury\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard The treatment of an injury or abnormality, by invasive means. By comparison, \b First Aid\b0  keeps a patient alive until surgery is possible, and \b Herb Lore\b0  allows for medicinal preparations to be administered which might help with long term recovery. (See \b HEALING\b0  on page 53)\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Ciphers\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
The knowledge of methods whereby the meaning of a message (verbal, written, or other) can be hidden from prying eyes. Use it to encode a message you want to safely send, or to decode a message written by someone else. \par
Note that when working with written messages, your effective rating in this skill is capped by your Literacy skill \endash  tests will usually be against the lower of the two.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Craft (Type)\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Making and repairing sophisticated tools and structures. A job that most people could figure out does not require the Craft skill, only an INT or DEX test. Use Craft for specialized work that needs training: Craft (Mechanic) to get a broken apparatus working \emdash  or to sabotage one beyond repair; Craft (Locksmith) to open a lock without a key, and so on.  \par
The Game Moderator decides whether a task requires Craft. Each Craft type is a separate skill: Blacksmith, Carpenter, Farmer, Woodworker, etc.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Disguise\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Alter your Protagonist\rquote s appearance, voice, posture, body language, and mannerisms to avoid recognition without drawing attention.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Dodge\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 30%\par
\pard Evading danger through instinct and reflexes. Use Dodge to avoid an attack. Against ranged weapons and explosives, Dodge is only useful to get to cover (see \b DODGING RANGED ATTACKS\b0  on page 52).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Drive\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Handling any ground-based vehicle or conveyance (carts, wagons, etc.) safely in a crisis. Unless the Game Moderator says otherwise, every Protagonist can drive safely in normal conditions. Use this skill to keep a vehicle safe in a tense pursuit or on dangerous terrain.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 First Aid\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard The initial treatment and stabilization of injuries. Use it to help a character recover lost Hit Points. By comparison, \b Chirurgury\b0  corrects a severe wound and Apothecary ensures long-term medical treatment and recovery. (See \b HEALING\b0  on page 53.)\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Folklore\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
Folklore is the knowledge of the customs and lore of the common people of region. It is used to deduce the proper way to enter a house, whether to walk around the field widdershins prior to planting winter wheat, or in what order to propitiate the saints. It\rquote s also useful when trying to understand the myths and legends of region, such as what creature is said to live in the lake or why the eastern face of the mountain has no trees.\par
At the Game Master\rquote s discretion, separate folklore skills for different regions may be used or the Game Master can apply a penalty the farther a protagonist travels from their home.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Forage/Hunt\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
Forage/Hunt is used to find edible food in the wilderness. The appropriate tools are required, such a bow, spear, or other weapon to hunt animals. It also covers dressing the prey and preparing it for storage.\par
A successful roll provides enough food for a group of four to eat for a week.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Foreign Court/Kingdom (Type)\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1 The feudal world is a vast and sprawling place, and while many people know some very basic details of each far-flung power \endash  a place name or two and where it is \endash  detailed knowledge is limited to those who have spent substantial time living, serving, or studying there.\par
This skill represents such deep understanding of the people, places, and common practices that are unique to one colonial outpost. Use it to recall details of the local climate, local peoples, history, and local government arrangement. It can also cover quirky beliefs or discoveries that have come to be common knowledge among residents.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Foreign Language (Type)\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
Fluency in another language. Each foreign language is a distinct skill. Having 20% allows halting conversations; at 50% your Protagonist speaks and reads like a native. The greater the skill, the greater the complexity of the information your Protagonist comprehends and the less time it takes. You don\rquote t need to roll a Foreign Language skill unless the Game Moderator says the situation is exceptionally difficult.\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Being able to speak a language doesn\rquote t necessarily mean you can read or write text in that language; attempts to do that are also determined by the \b Literacy\b0  skill. The Game Moderator might require separate rolls against both skills or a single roll applied across both tests, depending on the situation.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Harangue/Taunt\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
The art of either browbeating someone into agreeing with your point of view, or of enraging them to the point where they will lose control and act in an undisciplined way that is advantageous to you.\par
This technique is not a subtle attempt to convince someone through a well-reasoned argument (that\rquote s \b Persuade\b0 ). Nor is it a tempt to appeal to their sense of power and importance (that\rquote s \b Beguile\b0 ). Instead, Harangue/Taunt is all about bluster, shouting, and threats. But sometimes these can be more successful than other techniques, although the individuals on the receiving end are unlikely to enjoy the interaction quite so much.\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1 Taunting is a related discipline, namely an attempt to insult or belittle verbal opponents to the point where they lose their temper and say or do something rash (which they will usually later regret). In some cultures, this is a well-established way of winning an argument or establishing superiority in the minds of the community.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Herb Lore\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
Herb Lore is an understanding of herbs, the proper method to collect them, where to find them, when to find them, and what can be done with them. \par
The \b Alchemy\b0  skill is used to turn herbs into poultices, salves, and other useful products including medical preparations.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 History\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 Uncovering facts and theories about human antiquity. Use it to remember or find a key fact about the distant past, recognize an obscure reference, or comb through records that nobody without your deep education could find. History is a broad study of humanity.\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 In the Medieval Era, history can be as much about listening to chansons, gestae, and stories around the campfire as reading old scrolls in one of the few libraries in the world.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Homeland\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 Homeland represents a protagonist\rquote s general knowledge about their homeland. Who\rquote s in charge, basic geography, known power struggles, which lord owns a certain village, etc. \par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 History, Folklore, and other more specific skills should be used to gain in-depth knowledge.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Insight\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
Insight obtains information about a person \emdash  especially information the subject would rather conceal \emdash  through observation, conversation, or examining patterns of behavior and relationships. Use Insight to recognize signs of dishonesty from verbal cues and body language, gauge attitude and intentions, cultivate sources of information about a subject, determine what it would take to get a subject to cooperate, or recognize clues of what a subject wants to conceal. \par
\pard Insight can notice signs of mental illness but Reassure would be needed to assist with a specific malady. A subject who deliberately tries to deceive your Protagonist can attempt an opposed test comparing their Persuade against your Protagonist\rquote s Insight (see \b OPPOSED TESTS\b0  on page 45).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Literacy\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The ability to read and write your own native language and any other language you have learned. In this era not everyone is taught to be literate, despite it being important (perhaps even necessary) to performing certain jobs. If you want your Protagonist to be able to interpret or create documents, he or she will need to have at least a basic rating in this skill. As a shorthand, anyone with a Literacy skill below 10 is considered functionally \b illiterate\b0 ; a skill rating between 11 and 40 represents \b semi-literacy\b0 ; a rating above 40 denotes a \b fully literate\b0  individual.\par
The skill does not need to be purchased separately for each of the languages known; it is assumed that the basics of reading and writing common alphabets does not need to be re-learned. Note that in many cases where a document written in a foreign language needs to be comprehended, this will likely involve skill tests of BOTH Literacy and the requisite \b Foreign Language\b0  skill. It is the GM\rquote s discretion as to whether tests should involve a single die roll compared to both skills, or separate rolls against each.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Melee Weapons\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 30%\par
Lethal use of melee weapons and shields in combat. Use it to hurt or kill an opponent with a knife, axe, club, or other hand-held weapon.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Navigate\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
Finding your way quickly with maps, charts and tables, orienteering, compass, or dead reckoning.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Occult (Type)\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
The study of the supernatural as understood by human traditions, including things like magick, the hermetic tradition, and secret societies. Use Occult to examine and deduce the intent of a ritual, or to identify occult traditions, groups, grimoires, tools, symbols, or legends. Occult can never tell a Protagonist what\rquote s genuinely unnatural and what\rquote s just superstition or mythology. That\rquote s the province of the Unnatural skill.\par
Occult is the more academic counterpart to \b Folklore\b0 . Successful Folklore and Occult rolls could provide the same information, viewed through different filters.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Persuade\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 Changing another\rquote s deeply held decision or desire. Use Persuade to get your Protagonist\rquote s way when the subject is so stubborn, what your Protagonist wants is so valuable, or the deception is so flagrant that Charisma isn\rquote t enough. \par
\pard With Persuade, your Protagonist might convince a witness that what she saw was innocuous and not unnatural, talk a compound leader into helping you cover up an outbreak to avoid a mass panic, or draw useful information out of an unwilling subject. This skill also allows your Protagonist to resist persuasion and interrogation in opposed Persuade rolls (see \b OPPOSED TESTS\b0  on page 45).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Procuratio\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 A knowledge of how bureaucracies work and what kinds of forms, paperwork, journals, etc. it invariably generates. Use it to sift through detailed charters or pipe rolls to find that one quirky point that just doesn\rquote t seem to fit the usual pattern. \par
Use this skill to rapidly navigate your way adeptly through written records to find what\rquote s important. It can also be useful in determining forgeries. Forged charters are a common scheme that can catch someone just skinning documents off guard.\par
Note that this skill is primarily about interpreting information you have; if you need to actively go out and track down books, records, etc. that would be covered by either the \b Search\b0  skill, some combination of social skills, or perhaps \b Carouse \b0 (depending on the mode of searching).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Quadrivium\lang3081\f1\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 The Quadrivium represents part, along with the Trivium, of a medieval scholar\rquote s areas of study. The quadrivium encompasses the disciplines of the liberal arts: music, astronomy, arithmetic and geometry.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Ranged Weapons\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 The ability to accurately hit targets with ranged weapons such as Bows, Crossbows, and Slings.\par
This skill isn\rquote t used for thrown weapons like Spears \endash  those make use of the \b Athletics\b0  skill instead.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Reassure\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 Use this skill to understand the mental illness afflicting a person, help an afflicted person along the journey back to sanity, or talk someone down when the mental illness threatens to take hold.\par
You can also use this skill to assist in social interactions with someone, to calm them from an agitated state in order to extract information from them. You cannot use Reassure on yourself. \par
\pard Using Reassure to aid someone who suffered exposure to Unnatural forces might cost the reassuring Survivor SAN; see \b THREATS TO SAN\b0  on page 70\lang1033 .\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Religion (Type)\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
A detailed knowledge of one of the several common belief systems that are known to exist, each providing its own account of the divine and explanations for the ways of the observed natural world. \par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1 Use it to know the differences between the beliefs of varying denominations of the particular religion, or to be able to recite passages from common religious texts. It doesn\rquote t include knowledge of obscure or fringe beliefs associated with the religion; details of such hidden wisdom are covered by the relevant \b Occult\b0  skill instead.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Repair/Devise\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
With many settlements isolated by a day or more journey from each other, self-reliance is key. The ability to repair broken equipment or create impromptu fixes for unexpected break-downs is vital.\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1 Repair/Devise is not a craft skilled. It\rquote s designed to make some work just long enough to get the job done (hopefully). Many other \i Cthulhu Eternal\i0  settings use Craft (Jury-Rig). Repair/Devise takes the place of that in this setting.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Ride\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1 Handling, training, and riding an animal \emdash  horses, donkeys, camels, whatever. Use it to keep safe on an animal in a crisis and to keep riding animals safe, calm, and healthy.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Sailing (Type)\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1 Piloting, navigating, and captaining waterborne vehicles. Use it to keep a boat or ship safe in a crisis, such as through a storm or in a dangerous pursuit. Each vessel type is a separate skill: Small Boat, Ship, Canoe, etc.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Scavenge\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
The world is full of useful items, although most people don\rquote t know where to go looking for the good stuff. Use this skill to find and salvage helpful pieces of equipment or locate valuable resources like food and water. Anyone can find items in places where they are likely to be found (e.g., food in a larder); use this skill to find things in places where nobody else would think to look.\par
\pard Depending on the game setting and the scarcity of the item being sought, the difficulty of Scavenge tests and the quality of the items unearthed by successful rolls may vary. See \b SCROUNGING\b0  starting page 64.\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1 Note that efforts to rummage for information rather than items is handled by social or knowledge skills instead.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Search\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1 Finding things that are concealed or obscured from plain sight. Searching an abandoned dwelling may not require the Search skill, only time and effort, or a sufficiently high INT. Use Search to find an object that was hidden with the Stealth skill or is otherwise so well hidden or disguised that it needs an expert. The Game Moderator may roll the Search attempt, so you don\rquote t know whether your Protagonist succeeded or failed.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Siege Weapons\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
A large part of medieval warfare are sieges. Towns, castles, monasteries, cities, even islands can be besieged. \par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 This skill provides knowledge on how to use, maintain, and defend against the various siege weapons on the battlefield. It isn\rquote t just a skill for warrior classes, peasants are often press-ganged into serving on siege weapon crews.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Stealth\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard Concealing your presence or activities. Use it to hide a weapon, camouflage a position, conceal an occult amulet, pick a pocket, move silently, follow without being seen, or blend into a crowd. A Protagonist attempting Stealth can be detected only by an opposing Alertness or Search skill (see \b OPPOSED TESTS\b0  on page 45).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Swim\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 Most Protagonists can swim for leisure. Use the Swim skill in a dangerous crisis: going a long distance in choppy water, keeping a friend from drowning, or getting to a boat before the tentacled thing below grabs you.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Trivium\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 Trivium is the \ldblquote lesser\rdblquote  of the two liberal arts. It comprises rhetoric, grammar, and logic. It can be useful for player characters trying to make sense of all the information they\rquote ve been given.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Unarmed Combat\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 40%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 Self-defense. A fight between untrained combatants often involves more shoving and shouting than real violence. Use Unarmed Combat to hurt or kill an opponent with your Protagonist\rquote s bare hands (or feet, elbows, teeth, or head).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\fi-864\li864\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Unnatural\par
\pard\sa80\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 Knowledge of the fundamental, mind-shattering secrets of the universe. The things that slithered in the dark corners of the world and the cosmos beyond. Use it to remember, recognize, or research facts about the things humans consider unnatural. This goes far beyond the occult, because the Unnatural skill represents things that are real. Use it to sift through the darkest parts of myth and folklore and recognize which of it is true. \par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb120\sl276\slmult1\cf2\lang1033\b\f0\fs26 2.11\tab Detailed Description: Mental Damage from Harsh Upbringings\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 Protagonists that have grown up in difficult and brutal conditions are likely to have picked up some mental scarring along the way. This can leave them hardened to certain types of traumatic stimuli. It might also make them psychologically distant from those around them, or even afflicted with mental disorders.\par
\pard\sl276\slmult1 Mental Damage gained from a harsh early life can take several forms: \par
