\clbrdrl\brdrw10\brdrs\clbrdrt\brdrw10\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrw10\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrw10\brdrs \cellx10687\pard\intbl A Protagonist can take only one action per turn. In some settings, there might exist advanced weapons which may hit multiple targets, or one target multiple times, with a single roll (see \b LETHALITY RATING\b0  on page \lang3081 54\lang1033 ), but it\rquote s still just one action per turn. If this seems counterintuitive (\ldblquote a good brawler can throw three jabs a second!\rdblquote ) don\rquote t think of every roll as a single action but as a few seconds of fighting or moving.\cell\row\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 4.2\tab Attack Rolls\f1\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\fs22 An attack is a skill roll which inflicts damage, disarms or pins the target, depending on the attacker\rquote s action.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 4.2.1\tab Critical Hits and Fumbles\par
\pard\cf0\b0\f1 An attack roll that\rquote s a critical success (see page \lang3081 43\lang1033 ) is a \i critical hit\i0 . A critical hit inflicts double damage.\par
An attack roll that \i fumbles \i0 (see page \lang3081 43\lang1033 ) is bad news. The exact outcome remains up to the Game Moderator and can include:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 1.\tab A weapon malfunctions in some way, requiring 1D4 turns to fix\par
2.\tab A weapon drops and it takes a turn to pick it back up.\par
3.\tab The attacker accidentally hits a friend, a bystander, or himself / herself.\par
4.\tab The attacker stumbles and falls.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 4.2.2\tab Attack Modifiers\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 When you make an attack roll, it means the situation is out of control. Combat is chaotic and unpredictable even for the most highly trained fighters. The combatants\rquote  skill ratings and the luck of the dice usually tell everything you need to know.\par
Bonuses and penalties in combat apply only in extraordinary circumstances. The \b COMBAT MODIFIERS\b0  table, nearby, lists the likeliest modifiers. If they do apply, Attack bonuses stack up to a maximum +40%. There\rquote s no limit on penalties.\par
No matter the bonus or penalty, a roll of 01 always hits and a roll of 00 (100) always misses.\par
