\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 4.2.3\tab Surprise Attacks\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 If your Protagonist is out to kill someone who\rquote s unaware or helpless (and nobody is trying to stop you), that\rquote s hardly combat. You may not even need to make a roll.\par
\b TARGET IS TOTALLY HELPLESS \emdash  BOUND OR ASLEEP:\b0  No roll is needed to murder the target in one turn.\par
\b TARGET IS ACTIVE BUT UNAWARE AND COMBAT HAS NOT YET BEGUN:\b0  Make an attack roll at +20%. Any success is a critical hit. If it fails, the attack misses. Maybe your Protagonist flinched at the last instant or maybe the target moved. Work out the details with the Game Moderator.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 4.2.4\tab Firing Into A Crowd\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Use a \caps called shot\caps0  to hit a particular target in a crowd with a ranged attack. Otherwise a random member of the crowd takes the hit.\par
