\b STUN:\b0  Stun attacks startle and impair. While stunned, your Protagonist can\rquote t act. When it\rquote s your Protagonist\rquote s turn, you may attempt a \b CON\'d75\b0  test to recover and act normally next turn. If a single attack inflicts half of your Protagonist\rquote s \i current \i0 HP, the Protagonist is automatically stunned.\par
\b UNCONSCIOUSNESS:\b0  If your Protagonist is reduced to 2 or fewer HP, he or she falls unconscious. An unconscious Protagonist is helpless and can be killed with a single attack without having to roll. At 3 HP or more (or after an hour passes), the Protagonist regains consciousness.\par
\b PERMANENT INJURY:\b0  Any time your Protagonist is reduced to 2 or fewer HP, make a \b CON\'d75\b0  test. Failure indicates permanent injury. The Game Moderator selects a stat to be \i permanently \i0 reduced by the number on the \i lowest ten-sided die of the failed CON\'d75 \i0 roll. Stats can only be reduced in this way to a minimum score of 3. If STR or CON drop, adjust HP accordingly.\par
\b DEATH:\b0  If an attack brings your Protagonist to 0 HP, he or she is dead. HP do not go below 0.\par
