\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 4.11.5\tab Cold\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Protagonists can last for CON in minutes exposed to freezing temperatures unprepared, or CON\'d75 minutes if partially prepared. Fully prepared and well-equipped Protagonists can last CON hours.\par
After this, their bodies start to fail. Players must make a \b CON\'d75\b0  test every five minutes. Each failure reduces CON by 1. When a Protagonist\rquote s CON hits 1, the Protagonist can no longer move and suffers 1D8 HP cold damage every five minutes. Exposure to warmth and shelter restores 1 point of CON per minute. Hit Points heal normally.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 4.11.6\tab Starvation and Thirst\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Protagonists deprived of food for longer than a week will begin to die of starvation. Each week, make a test against \b CON\'d72\b0  or a relevant Survival skill (whichever is higher), failure leading to a loss of CON. For the first week without nourishment the loss is 1D2, the next week 1D4, then 2D4, 3D4 and so on.\par
Surviving without water is much more difficult. For the first 24 hours without hydration there are no effects, but for each day thereafter the Protagonist must make a test against \b CON\'d72\b0  or a relevant Survival skill (whichever is higher). Failure means a loss of 1D4 STR and 1D4 CON. If a water supply is re\u8208?established these points will return at a rate of 1D2 STR and 1D2 CON each day.\par
If at any point the Protagonist\rquote s STR or CON drops to zero, he or she has died of starvation or thirst.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 4.12\tab The Aftermath\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 When the smoke clears and the fighting stops, it\rquote s time for the Game Moderator to look to the consequences of combat. There are \i always \i0 consequences.\par
\pard First, violence damages sanity. Unless your Protagonist is a hardened operator, getting into a deadly fight calls for a Sanity roll. So does getting hurt. So does killing someone. (See \b THREATS TO SAN\b0  on page \lang3081 70\lang1033 .)\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 Next, was anyone killed or badly hurt? If so \'85 who\rquote s going to come looking for them? \par
\pard\keep\keepn\s1\fi-432\li432\sb360\sl276\slmult1\cf1\b\f0\fs28 5.0\tab Equipment\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 Most equipment that your Protagonist will buy, find or use does not require any special rules \endash  if you have the equipment, and it is in working order then you can use it (possibly with a skill or stat test) to do things. Some items that are poorly made or worn-out may incur a penalty (see the box nearby).\par
Obtaining equipment can be as simple as purchasing it in a store (assuming such commerce exists in the game setting); alternatively, it can involve scrounging around trying to piece together usable items from junk.\par
