\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 6.1\tab Hit Points and Armor\par
\pard\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 Each vehicle counts as a Huge target (see \b HUGE\b0 , page \lang3081 58\lang1033 ). It takes damage from unarmed attacks and small weapons such as knives and clubs only when the Game Moderator thinks it makes sense.\par
A vehicle that loses \b half\b0  its Hit Points is badly damaged. It can\rquote t be operated without a relevant skill test (depending on the type of vehicle). The next time such a test \i fumbles\i0 , the vehicle fails altogether until repaired. Repairing a damaged vehicle requires time, parts, and successful application of one or more skill tests. Even if repaired, the vehicle might now qualify as \lquote heavily worn\rquote  or \lquote junk\rquote  (see \b\caps Pre-Loved Items and Spoiled Goods\b0\caps0 , page \lang3081 64\lang1033 ).\par
A vehicle that loses \i all\i0  of its Hit Points is demolished. It will never function again.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 6.1.1\tab Speed\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\lang3081\b0\f1 When comparing Vehicles, there is a range of different vehicle speeds. A vehicle with a \lquote Fast\rquote  rating grants a +20% bonus to any \b Drive\b0  or \b Sailing\b0  test to pursue or escape. A \lquote Slow\rquote  vehicle incurs a \u8722?20% penalty instead, while a \lquote Very Slow\rquote  vehicle attracts a \u8722?40% penalty. An \lquote Average\rquote  rating confers no modifier.\par
A vehicle that\rquote s notorious for poor handling or that\rquote s in bad shape might counts as \lquote heavily worn\rquote  or \lquote junk\rquote  (see above) at the GM\rquote s discretion.\par
