\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 7.3\tab Explore the Loss\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 When your Protagonist loses SAN, take a second to describe it. If the Protagonist loses a few points, how does that look to the people around him or her? Does the Protagonist jump or cry out in terror? Does the Protagonist stare in shock? Does the Protagonist back away involuntarily? If your Protagonist kills someone and loses no SAN, what does that say about the Protagonist?\par
What are the long-term effects of repeatedly losing SAN? What strong beliefs or motivations are eroding as your Protagonist\rquote s SAN falls? The game is more potent when you play out those details and let them shape your Protagonist.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 7.4\tab Threats to SAN\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 The three major threats to SAN are \i Violence\i0 , \i Helplessness \i0 and the \i Unnatural\i0 .\par
These categories can overlap. Being tied up and tortured might trigger both Violence and Helplessness. It\rquote s up to the Game Moderator to decide which aspects affects the Protagonist.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 7.4.1\tab Violence\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Killing other humans is inherently harmful to sanity. While wrestling and punching people is within biological norms, bludgeoning someone to death is not instinctive. Violence can drive you insane if you\rquote re not careful.\par
In combat, you must make a SAN test for a trauma \i the first time it happens in that fight\i0 . Outside of combat, every individual incident triggers its own SAN loss.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 7.4.2\tab Helplessness\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 The essential human impulse is to act. True inactivity is unwholesome to the human psyche.\par
Note that helplessness often makes violence worse, just like violence makes helplessness worse.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 7.4.3\tab The Unnatural\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Finally there\rquote s the unnatural, the inhuman things of the Cthulhu Mythos that haunt the edges of existence. The unnatural troubles us because it is wholly outside of human experience. It wounds our sense of connection to the world by causing huge gaps in understanding.\par
This is why your Unnatural skill limits maximum SAN. The more you understand of mankind\rquote s \i actual \i0 position in the cosmos, the harder it is to navigate in the \lquote real\rquote  world.\par
If a Protagonist faces the Unnatural and loses 0 SAN, it may mean the Protagonist has adapted to the reality of the Unnatural in some small way \emdash  or it may mean simple denial, refusing to admit the Unnatural experience was real. It\rquote s up to the player.\par
