\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 Creature stat-blocks in Gumshoe are relatively brief, consisting of ratings for: Athletics, Health, Scuffling, Hit Threshold, Alertness Modifier, Stealth Modifier, Weapon, Armor, and sometimes Stability Loss. The tables below give a (rough) idea of how these ratings can be carried across to \i Cthulhu Eternal\i0  creature statistics. Because Gumshoe is quite a different system, some creativity will be required to fill in statistics like INT, POW, etc. since Gumshoe typically doesn\rquote t measure such attributes for creatures.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 13.1\tab Athletics Rating\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 In general, a creature can be assumed to have a \i Cthulhu Eternal\i0  Athletics skill equal to its Gumshoe Athletics rating \'d7 12%. Physical statistics like STR, DEX, and CON can \endash  if needed \endash  be inferred from this. A higher Gumshoe Athletics rating almost certainly means one or more of those stats will be well above average.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 13.2\tab Health Rating\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 In general, a creature in \i Cthulhu Eternal\i0  will have 2 Hit Points for every single point of Gumshoe Health Rating. For example, a Gumshoe monstrosity with a Health Rating of 10 will have 20 HP in \i Cthulhu Eternal\i0 .\par
